  "prompt": "How do I recognize a fake solar panel?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help recognize a fake solar panel:\n\n1. Price indicators\n- If the price seems too good to be true, it probably is\n- Extremely low prices compared to market rates suggest potential counterfeits\n\n2. Physical inspection\n- Check for poor quality manufacturing\n- Look for uneven or sloppy soldering\n- Examine surface quality and finishing\n- Check for inconsistent cell sizes or alignment\n\n3. Documentation verification\n- Request and verify manufacturer's certification\n- Check for legitimate serial numbers\n- Examine warranty documentation\n- Verify company's reputation and registration\n\n4. Performance testing\n- Conduct power output tests\n- Compare actual performance with manufacturer specifications\n- Use professional testing equipment if possible\n\n5. Purchase from reputable sources\n- Buy from authorized dealers\n- Check manufacturer's official distributor list\n- Read customer reviews and ratings\n- Use established online and offline marketplaces\n\n6. Technical specifications\n- Compare specifications with industry standards\n- Check efficiency ratings\n- Verify technical details like wattage and voltage\n\n7. Warning signs\n- Lack of clear contact information\n- No physical address for the manufacturer\n- Minimal or suspicious online presence\n- Limited technical documentation\n\nAlways research thoroughly and consult professionals when making significant solar panel investments.",
